repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
This PR allows types to define their own `generate_incref` (etc) type functions, with `put_incref` (etc) deferring to those functions. The idea being that mixed C struct/Python types can be created more easily and make use of the existing code for generating reference counting.

Right now this PR defines the such functions for `PyObject` and `MemoryviewSlice`. It's really designed to support https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/3346, so should probably be reviewed before that PR.

This PR does shouldn't change anything user-visible (hopefully) - it's just a change in structure to make other changes easier.

commit.message:
Moved generation of reference counting into PyrexTypes

The idea being that struct-types like memoryviews
can generate their own reference counting code
using a common interface with Python objects
Removed no_pyobject_cast, cleaned up some putvars

Replace put_exprnode_xxxref with a function on Exprnode

To prevent Code.py having to know that nodes exist

Removed memoryview giveref

It was causing problems because no memoryviews were givereffed in
the old code

Made memoryviews more separate

Since they often don't want to be reference counted when
pyobjects do

Removed autoloading of utility code

Wasn't necessary and just seemed like extra work

title: Make reference counting more generic
